    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="723"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d723">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1174</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MGT1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marye</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Petrograd</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-06">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 5, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11:45 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Russian Government officially notifies Embassy that it has placed mines in zone
                    from 58° 50’ north latitude and to east of twenty-first meridian, also at
                    entrance of Gulf of Riga and around Åland Islands and consequently entrance and
                    exit of Finnish and Riga gulfs forbidden.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MGT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marye</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
